President Donald J. Trump has issued a proclamation designating July 21 through July 27, 2019, as Captive Nations Week. This week is dedicated to reaffirming the United States' support for those fighting against oppressive regimes and advocating for freedom, justice, and the rule of law. The proclamation condemns repressive governments that deny their people basic rights and uses various means to control and suppress them. The United States stands with those who are oppressed and urges governments worldwide to respect the rights of every individual and establish representative government. The proclamation also highlights the privileges and blessings enjoyed by Americans due to their Constitution, which protects fundamental rights. President Trump calls upon all Americans to reaffirm their commitment to supporting those striving for liberty, justice, and the rule of law.